{{italic title}} The '''''Sacred Books of the East''''' is a monumental 50-volume set of English translations of Asian religious writings, edited by [[Max Müller]] and published by the [[Oxford University Press]] between 1879 and 1910. It incorporates the essential sacred texts of [[Hinduism]], [[Buddhism]], [[Taoism]], [[Confucianism]], [[Zoroastrianism]], [[Jainism]], and [[Islam]].
All of the books are in the [[public domain in the United States]], and most or all are in the public domain in many other countries.<ref>[http://www.sacred-texts.com/sbe/ sacred-texts.com]</ref> Electronic versions of all fifty volumes are widely available online.
