. W. West]] || [[Zoroastrian Middle Persian|Pahlavi]] Texts, vol. 5 of 5. Marvels of [[Zoroastrianism]]. |- ! 48 |Hindu |1904 || [[George Thibaut]] || The Vedanta-Sutras, vol. 3 of 3, with the commentary of [[Râmânuja]]. |- ! 49 |Bud |1894 || [[Edward Byles Cowell]], F. [[Max Müller]] and [[Takakusu Junjiro]] || [[Buddhism|Buddhist]] [[Mahayana|Mahâyâna]] Texts. Part 1. The [[Buddhacarita|Buddha-karita of Asvaghosha]], translated from the [[Sanskrit]] by E. B. Cowell. Part 2. The [[Infinite Life Sutra|larger Sukhâvatî-vyûha]], the [[Amitabha Sutra|smaller Sukhâvatî-vyûha]], the [[Diamond Sutra|Vagrakkhedikâ]], the larger [[Heart Sutra|Pragñâ-pâramitâ-hridaya-sûtra]], the smaller [[Heart Sutra|Pragñâ-pâramitâ-hridaya-sûtra]], translated by F. Max Müller. The [[Amitayurdhyana Sutra|Amitâyur dhyâna-sûtra]], translated by J. Takakusu. |- ! 50 |index |1910 || [[Moriz Winternitz]], with a preface by [[Arthur Anthony Macdonell]] || General index to the names and subject-matter of the sacred books of the East. |}
