{{use dmy dates|date=September 2016}}
'''Vladimír Kompánek''' (28 October 1927 in [[Rajec]] &ndash; 20 January 2011) was a [[Slovakia|Slovak]] sculptor and painter. He won the [[Herder Prize]] in 1967.<ref>[http://www.osobnosti.sk/index.php?os=zivotopis&ID=59333 www.osobnosti.sk]</ref>

Between 1947 - 1949 he studied at the [[Slovak Technical University]] in [[Bratislava]], then from 1949 - 1954 at the College of Fine Arts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.osobnosti.sk/index.php?os=zivotopis&ID=59333 |title=Vladimír Kompánek &#124; osobnosti.sk &#124; životopisy, diela, tvorba, články, linky |publisher=osobnosti.sk |date= |accessdate=2011-11-29}}</ref>

His wooden sculptures draw ideas from the rural environment. Kompánek also creates the concept of "protective deities", symbols which appear in his works. symbols. A frequent motif he uses is a woman and field characters and carnival masks. He is also a maker of wooden toys.

